<br>
And getting back to the topic-at-large, Trab.. I think it's safe to assume that parental guidance (be it either passive or aggressive) is critical in forming ANY child's sense of morality.  A lack of it allows for too much of a course deviation from the rest of the civilized herd - the child's sense of right and wrong could be horribly and possibly dangerously skewed.<br>
